incident_updates.body: Tableau Engineers have confirmed that the solution put in place to mitigate the issue in Tableau Cloud causing recently moved content to become unavailable, was successful. This incident is now considered resolved.

Tableau Engineers are continuing work to mitigate this impact.  More detailed information can be found in the following KB article:
https://kb.tableau.com/articles/issue/tableau-cloud-error-page-unavailable-and-content-missing-after-moving-content-and-deleting-original-project

Tableau Engineers are investigating an issue within Tableau Cloud that is impacting a subset of our users.  We advise Tableau Cloud users not to delete projects until this issue is resolved.  If content is moved from one project to another, and the previous project is deleted, content in the new project may become unavailable.

We are working to identify the scope of impact and implement a solution as quickly as possible. We thank you for your patience; our next update will be when new information becomes available.
